      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ELBOWS ALLEYWAY (7) took the sit on the lead from an outside box but levelled up and drew clear to score (20.13) at this track in TG1-4W over 342m. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. Form reads well for this. MOUNTAIN HAWK (1) turned in a plain run last time when sixth at Gawler over 400m behind Ribery (23.77) in a Grade 6/MDN. Placed at her previous run. Safe beginner who draws ideally on the inside. Should play a prominent role. NOT THE GRAVY (8) had been racing in honest fashion recording three placings in a row before finishing fourth (23.49) at Gawler latest. Deserves plenty of respect. SOUTH GIRLS (2) has ability and finds the right scenario to bounce back.",
